\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 
If we just leave that for a minute, you said you have a younger brother who was born nine years later?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15615334\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Yes. There is a sort of tragedy about that, which I don\rquote t specially want to go into. [Brother left 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}St. Albans{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 at 16 to join the Northern Rhodesian Police] But, I mean, it is important, but I don\rquote t feel like going into all of that, because \'85 he came to a very untimely, early death. [He was murdered in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Africa
{\*\xmlclose}] And it \'85 it made my mother very bitter and sad about it. It happened at a time when I\rquote d got young children, and I could, perhaps, have prevented it, to some degree, by \'85 I mean, I don\rquote 
t think I can, but I actually went for quite serious counselling too, to get out of that. And the \'85 I did get out of it \'85 I mean, we\rquote re touching a very sensitive nerve here.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Leave it, then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15615334\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 
But I will just say that there was a kind of guilt about the fact that I was somehow an accomplice in murdering my brother, which was heavy stuff, by a Kleini
an analyst that came with me. And we worked that through. And the analyst got me to see, she was a specialist, as it turned out, in lone children who were too close to their mother during the War. She\rquote 
d worked with that particular problem. Now, rightly or wrongly, she put me into that category, and argued that the birth of my brother, immediately after the end of the War, was a sort of shock to me, because I\rquote d been the only one there, and that I
\rquote d got deep hidden resentments against him. Well, you know what they\rquote re like, I don\rquote t know whether this is true or not. But she got rid of whatever resentments might have been there, and it was a tragic \'85
 a tragic sadness. He was under my shadow too much, he tried to develop his own identity, and he just went wrong, and it just \'85
 just very unfortunate. But I think, just to say that, there was this kind of thing in the family, is probably enough, without going any further.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 
Yes. Yes. Sure. Do you feel you can talk about him as a child? Or do you want to \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15615334\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Well, I don\rquote t remember much about that, you see, because \'85
 and that was probably part of it, whether it was selective memory. But I really don\rquote t remember much about him at all. I think that \'85 I mean, a theory would be that when he was born, I came back to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London
{\*\xmlclose}, and I \'85 I \'85 I was hardly aware he existed, when I was going to this {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} prep. school, and then going on to \'85 to St. Alban
\rquote s, because I would have been \'85 let me see \'85 if he was born in 1945, or \rquote 44, then \'85 although I was \'85 yes, he w
as sort of five or so when I went off to the public school. And I was just very busy, and had all my friends, and I think, really, that my mother and he \'85
 that was the kind of the home life. And I, very soon, used the home simply as a kind of base. I was off with my friends and doing things in the holidays, and was leading my own kind of life, and didn\rquote 
t kind of get sucked in, in the way that he later complained about. Because he, then, of course, was a young \'85 growing up in the sixties, and my parents, I think, couldn\rquote t cope with the sixties. They just couldn\rquote 
t cope with dope and all the rest of it. And I had no idea about this until afterwards, but I think he had a very bad time and reacted against that. And that was one of the reasons that, you know, he went off. So, but I\rquote ve no idea really. It
\rquote s extraordinary how little I can tell you about \'85 I know I\rquote ve got photographs of me taking pictures of him in bed with his teddy, almost like a kind of pet. But there\rquote s a huge difference, you see, nine years.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Yes, absolutely. So can 
we talk, then, a bit about your teenage years, if you like, because you suddenly sound like you grew up, and you had lots of friends, having had a period when you were feeling bullied and so on earlier in your childhood. You sound like you had a very conf
ident time when you were in your teens.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15615334\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 I think the secret was that I got good at running, and, you know, it\rquote s a wonderful \'85
 you know, support, that the younger kids, if you\rquote re running for the school, or winning records and things, you get huge status, and everyone sort of \'85 you know, looks up to you, in a quite ridiculous way. So, and also, I \'85
 I managed the work okay. I mean, not \'85 not marvellously, I don\rquote t think, but, you know, enough to get by. And so I did things like school plays and, you know, a
ll of that. And I look back, there was a good crowd of friends, we all went off cycling in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}France{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 when we were 16, you know, with hardly any money \'85 \'a315, I think, was what we needed for a fortnight! Ate nothing but bananas for the last t
wo days! But there was, you know, that sort of feeling of being with a crowd of good friends, one in particular, who I still know, and I still keep up with. And \'85 the athletics being a thread \'85
 that sort of held my identity together, I suspect. You know, a lot of it was the sort of \'85 you know, the kind of lads \'85
 who were out boozing and smoking, I was a bit Puritanical about it, because of training, you see, one was obsessed about training, and, you know \'85 you learnt a lot there. So in the holidays, although I spent a lot of time, quite seriously training, I
\rquote d got access to another school\rquote s playing fields near where I lived at home, you see, and I\rquote d go up there and regularly thrash around and do all that. And that, in a sense, kept me out of mischief, and al
so, perhaps delayed the adolescence. I don\rquote t know. You know, because I actually was not doing the \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 
So would you do that on your own, or would there be other friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15615334\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 No, on my own. No, no. The whole point about athletics is that it\rquote s a very single thing. You\rquote 
d be obsessed about time and \'85 yes, you\rquote d have a training regime, which you\rquote d have to run so many laps or whatever it was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 
And has that continued into your adult life, that interest in running and athletics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15615334\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Yeah. I mean, oh yes, come the Olympic Games, I\rquote m sort of glued to the \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 
But what about you, personally, as a participant?
