ed to go down to my aunt in Cornwall for long holidays, through much of the summer, and I have this feeling of going, being on my own, going for long walks, there\rquote 
s a feeling that comes back, on one side of my memories, certainly before the age of 14. And then being sort of, you know, athletics, and \'85 I remember, I used to have a kind of \'85 a sort of mental cleansing exercise, when \'85
 if I got into some kind of embarrassing thing, as one does as a teenager, or was in some kind of trouble, I would sort of focus my mind on actually running a race, and do that race in my head, and that would somehow cleanse the embarrassment. It\rquote 
