\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15615334\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 No. I mean, I think the most extraordinary thing about my family is that \'85 my mother was clearly ambivalent about 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and her relatives. Because she\rquote d married up, she wasn\rquote t really keen on being friendly to the rest of her family, I don
\rquote t think. There was a huge disjunction between the ideology, which is, \'93We love each other\'94, but in actual practice \'85 and I picked that up very early on, that there\rquote 
s all this family ideology guff, but in practice, they never came. And in practice, it wasn\rquote t my mother that put up my grandmother or grandfather, her parents, it was others. And I\rquote ve heard, of course, that\rquote s going back, but I\rquote 
ve heard my aunt say that \'93Jeannie was always on about what a wonderful family and everything, but what did she do for them?\'94 So it could have been that she was protecting her little \'85 you know, cosy world of resp
