chool, was attracted to the Air Force side of it, because there was much less \'85 I\rquote ve always been sort of slightly mocking of the discipline and everything, but Air Force, the guy that ran that was a really laid back bloke so \'85
 and I got keen on \'85 there were all kinds of perks. I mean, we could \'85
 we could pass this off on Proficiency Tests, so, of course, we had to sit in classrooms and learn about the meteorology, rather than, you know, rushing around the country with guns and stuff, which is what the Army 
people were doing! So we were thought to be the slightly elite, you know, the clever ones, that went and did this. And then there was flying, of course, you couldn\rquote t do the Air Force without \'85
