t into this bonking culture. I was a bit miffed about this, but it was fun. And then we got across to Canada, and we went to a place called London, Ontario, and the Canadians were \'85
 we were very scornful about the Colonials, which, basically, would get us into big trouble to talk about Colonials, but they had to be taught to be kind of officers and gentlemen, and we just knew, of course! And they were a little \'85 I rememb
er, we used to have lectures on how you eat peas, and things like that!
