\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 What was Jan\rquote 
s background? Was it similar to your own, or very different?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15615334\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 
No. She comes from a very long-established middle-class family of some substance. Her great-aunt was Beatrice Webb, and so books have been written about her family. This book called, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 
Destined to be Wives}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 , which was written about the Webbs and \'85 and it was a \'85 when I got married, I was given the family tree [the Potters from Liverpool] that goes right back, and it
\rquote s just that everybody is related to \'85 there was Malcolm Muggeridge, they\rquote re all \'85 it\rquote s all a very Cambridgey family. And their grandfather was a Fellow of Trinity, and a Member of the Royal Society. And her mother had been at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cambridge{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} too, and possibly \'85 well, I\rquote m not sure about her grandmother, but certainly her mother. So very strong 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cambridge{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} family, very well-established, with strong kind of family connections to a particular type of \'85
 you know, bourgeois English people. But her father was a Scot, farmer. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 So where had she grown up?
