s father had farmed, in Southern Uplands of Scotland. But she wasn\rquote t \'85 but her mother was a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Cambridge{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 person. So what happened was that, after the War, her father, my father-in-law, bought the land that \'85 from his father-in-law, down in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Dorset{\*\xmlclose}
, and started to farm there. And so from after the War, she was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Dorset{\*\xmlclose}, and went to school at Sherbourne.
