\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15615334\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Sort of \'85 mmm \'85 dangerous! (LAUGHS) I don\rquote t believe in revolutions. I believe in doing one\rquote 
s best at the lowest possible level, but hopefully in a framework that is not too \'85 interventionist. So \'85 I actually do approve, quite a lot, of Euro laws to set up a framework in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Brussels{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and then subsidiarity down at the lowest possible level, so, you know, roll on. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Wales{\*\xmlclose} and 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Scotland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, let them do it, and make a cock up, and be unequal, because they will be unequal. You\rquote 
ve got to allow the cock-ups to take place, and then for the cock-ups to be discovered, and say, \'93You mustn\rquote t do that again\'94. So it\rquote s going from cock-up to cock-up, basically, I suppose. A lot of the good that\rquote 
s done, I discovered, in terms of, you know, the things that I approve of, are done by the enemy by mistake. I mean, the great \'85 I was \'85 in my earlier years, was very keen on sort of, you know, the freedom of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Africa{\*\xmlclose} and, you know, anti-Colonialism, it was all done by the Conservatives, MacMillan. And so many things were done, but, you know \'85 and one noticed they\rquote 
re scared to hell of some things, so they do it, you know, to sort of to make a concession. So a bit on the world-weary side, but believing that people \'85 populist, a sceptical populist, is what I\rquote d call myself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 I was going to ask you, but I think we\rquote 
