t know why. It\rquote s to do with stress and things. And in the late eighties, I had a bad attack of it, which coincided with sort of, you know, the sort of the thing with Jan perhaps and she
 went off to conferences and things, and my stomach really went bad, and I had lots of tests and I don\rquote t know what it was, and I couldn\rquote 
t eat anything, and I had a miserable time. And in the end, you know, I got into the hospital after about a year and a half of it, and the guy said, \'93Well, I really don\rquote t \'85 let me assure you, you don\rquote t have cancer of the stomach\'94
, which I had never realised I\rquote d been worrying about, but that shows how bad it had seemed to be.
