s, and I taught \'85 just sort of problems. I mean, I had one, I called it \'93Race, Resources and Religion\'94, which was some of the issues I was interested in, but I could have made it Race Relations and {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
Third World{\*\xmlclose} development, and \'85 I don\rquote t know why Religion was there! And I, I \'85 what else did I talk about? Yeah, I did a lot on Africa in the early years, I did some {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Africa{\*\xmlclose}
, because I brought the geography in there. And gradually, it changed towards \'85 you know, Social Structure in Modern Britain, or, yo
u know, The World We Live In, or something like that. And it would become more sort of sociology, current affairs, to some degree. Wide reading of it, all kinds of stuff. It was very good. I was going to say I was teaching what I was researching.
