\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15615334\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Yes, that\rquote s right. And they couldn\rquote t take it. So \'85 and I think \'85 I\rquote 
ve always worried a bit about sociologists who are lifting up the stone and watching the wriggling creatures underneath. And whether you do that kindly, or whether \'85 in a kindly way, or whether you do that in 
a rather destructive way, I think is a thing that used to worry a lot of people about sociology. And critics would say, you know, \'93You\rquote re just causing trouble, actually. You\rquote re destructively de-mystifying\'94. So if you\rquote re \'85
 I don\rquote t think Jan liked that. Jan \endash  the nice word would be de-mystifying, and a bad one would be piss-taking. And she thought that I was too much, taking too much pleasure in robbing people, stripping people of their delusions. That\rquote 
s a trouble between us. It\rquote s interesting, I met a young woman now, coming along later today, [Sara Philpott, the artist] who finds one of the most charming things about me is that I can do that. In all those years, Jan found it the most \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 So what\rquote s your response, then, to Jan 
\'85 and to whoever, now, about that remark?
