\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15929336\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Anyway, one of the difficult things about trying to explain what I w
as doing is that there were all these strands intermingling, and I was like different people. So that there was a world of difference between the managers and directors theme, which we\rquote ve hardly talked about \'85
 the geography theme, and the planning theme, and the urban sociology theme. And they were all very different. But, and also, I was building up my teaching. I just can\rquote t imagine how I did it. But I did become a professor in \'85
 what, 1971, it started officially from 1st January 1972, so I suppose I got my recognition for all this work. But there are other things too. One of the points I should make is that \'85 I\rquote 
ve been extraordinarily fortunate in being able to write easily and quickly. So I was able to write an article almost without any change. I could sit down and simply write it, I hardly changed it at all. And people say that I can write convincingly and 
\'85 with a style that\rquote s easy to read. But that is \'85 I accept that is a lot to thank my English teachers for or whatever. But I have a feel for words, and I like writing, I enjoy writing. It\rquote s a pleasure to do it, and it\rquote 
