\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid15929336\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 
Well, there was all kinds of strands to it. I mean, an obvious one was that Claire was getting a proper decent salary, but wasn\rquote t actually respected by the graduate students. \'93Why is she getting \'85 she\rquote 
s not that better than us. Why aren\rquote t we getting \'85 we\rquote re just toiling away on no money at all, and she\rquote s the kind of privileged one\'94. So that was, she couldn\rquote t do anything about that, she was embarra
ssed about that, but, you know, she did make blunders, which they were quick to notice and then, you know, \'93There she is, being paid this by you, and she\rquote s not that marvellous\'94. I think \'85
 from competition, like sort of competitive siblings for father\rquote s attention, in a way. Frances Evans was \'85 how shall I say? Very strongly committed to the Feminist position. That\rquote 
s putting it at its weakest! And she saw male chauvinist plots in everything, and did cause a lot of \'85 distress to various people.
