ve idea that I would write a book showing the variety of incentives that people had to work hard, the assumption being that an artist would be working in a quite different way from a barrister, from an academic, from a \'85
 top businessman or whatever, or a General. And that Mrs. Thatcher\rquote s notion that the rich would only work hard if you reduced taxes, and the poor will only work hard if you raise taxes, well, you know, in a sense \'85
 it was nonsense. Now, I then did this small study I mentioned before, of young yuppies, they might be \'85
