\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid5903709\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 It\rquote s described at the back of the book. There\rquote s a sort of \'85 ironic \'85 in fact, people - I can
\rquote t resist telling you this story! - I wrote what I called \'93An Appendix on Method\'94, which was a joke. And it was a joke on purposive sampling, because I could have just got my friends. But then I thought, \'93Well, you can\rquote 
t write a sociology book based on, you know, chats to your friends\'94, well, you could, but it would be a bit \'85 my conscience. Because I\rquote ve got friends that I\rquote ve known through my life, that have 
gone successful in all kinds of spheres, and I could have got a perfectly adequate collection of people that way. But my conscience prevented it. Instead of just friends, it was through contacts. I needed a good surgeon, and so I asked about and said, you
