\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid5903709\charrsid2767477 Ray:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 It\rquote s a much more difficult question to answer, that, because it\rquote 
s not as if there are giants that one could choose to say, \'93It\rquote s this giant rather than that giant\'94. In terms of the big ideas, as I say, I mentioned these \'85 the Feminism and the psychoanalysis. But \'85 \'85 I suppose one \'85
 often, I found this also in teaching, one gets more from \'85 sometimes from sociologists that are clearly wrong, and one is amazed, because some people think, \'93How can we get beyond that?\'94 So it\rquote s not that one\rquote s inspired, one\rquote 
s irritated. I think that\rquote s probably the case. There are a number of people who have written about things, and I think, \'93How can they possibly believe that that\rquote s so? Is this really what sociologists are \'85
 surely you can do better than this!\'94 It sounds a bit arrogant, but it\rquote s simply that it\rquote s not very convincing, a lot of what one reads. So one feels that \'85 a bit depressed about \'85
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 Michele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 :\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1197548\charrsid2767477 So is there anyone, specifically, who you
\rquote d name, as someone who\rquote s made you go off in one direction, because of something you\rquote ve read?
