s kept all these balls, well, not all in the air, some of them have crashed down \'85 but I think the strength of my approach to sociology has been a very divergent sort of line that\rquote s seen connections, and the fact that I\rquote ve really spent 
months talking to really poor people in the Isle of Sheppey, over a period of ten years, and also swanned around with the Lords and the Bishops and the captains of industry, and the Inner Clubs and stuff, means that one gets a kind of a view about the soc
iety you\rquote re living in, by your own life, not just by your research, but just by the sort of different areas you\rquote ve been in.
